  #cuando.content
    :markdown
      **MMHL_TJ** is a 3 day laboratory coordinated by
      [Michael Trigilio](http://visarts.ucsd.edu/faculty/michael-trigilio)
      and [Leslie García](http://lessnullvoid.cc), addressed to hardware/software developers,
      makers, musicians, composers, interactive designers, artists and anyone
      interested in DIWO music creation processes, in which we are seeking to
      develop stand-alone systems such as:

      - Theremins
      - 8- and 16-bit step sequencers
      - Atari punk consoles
      - Analog modeling synthesizers
      - Tone and effect generators

      And its interaction with optical, biological and mechanic  interfaces.

      ![Photo por Rockajoint](/img/mmhl03.jpg)

      A designated space for live act sessions will be set up during the AMF
      festival where the results will be presented and people would be able to
      interact with the devices developed during the workshop.

